    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-10T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="441"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163P92/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dooman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-11T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 11, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 11—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. Department’s 248, August 9, 8 p.m.<note n="38" xml:id="d441fn38">Not
                        printed.</note> On July 13 I addressed to the Minister for Foreign Affairs a
                    formal note emphatically objecting to continued occupation of Palmetto
                    Presbyterian Mission property at Soochow and asking that arrangement be made for
                    compensation for losses. A copy of the note was forwarded to the Department with
                    my despatch No. 4036, July 14.<note n="38" xml:id="d441fn39">Not printed.</note>
                    I asked the Foreign Office today to expedite reply.</p>
                <p>Shanghai please repeat to Chungking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dooman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
